cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with Device-to-Device (D2D) communications and traffic offloading in cellular networks. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves optimizing the transmit power to minimize energy consumption. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it introduces a user-centric proactive caching policy to control energy costs. It may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with content delivery traffic and caching files. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves offloading traffic via D2D links.
